45
00:03:38,550 --> 00:03:42,410
So these are very expensive. And instead of having unlimited risk,

46
00:03:42,650 --> 00:03:48,050
we can actually buy the farther out of the money put to cap our risk off.

47
00:03:49,430 --> 00:03:53,450
Now obviously, because there is steep skew, this put,

48
00:03:53,690 --> 00:03:57,140
let's say is going to be 40%, is going to be very expensive.

49
00:03:57,980 --> 00:04:01,220
So we're going to be giving a lot of our edge back to the market.

50
00:04:02,790 --> 00:04:08,130
